FBIS3-54249 "drnes016_l_94024" FBIS-NES-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 ISRAEL Houses Allegedly Damaged by IDF Missiles in Gaza TA2401190094 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in Hebrew 1800 GMT 24 Jan 94 TA2401190094 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Iman Abu-Sita, suspected of involvement in the murder of David Bublin and Hayim Weizmann in Ramla, was captured in Rafah today. The residents of the Rafah neighborhood where the capture took place said the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] used anti-tank missiles and that seven houses were damaged, one of which was completely destroyed. The IDF's Southern Command's reaction was that during an initiated operation in Rafah, grenades were used to break into and clear a house, after which an armed wanted man was captured.
